&nbsp;<\/div>\r\n\r\n<div>You can therefore easily enrich the description of your products. In addition, you can choose the character to be displayed between the values of the same feature.<\/div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>\r\n\r\n<div>If you also use our <strong>&quot;Advanced Search 5&quot;<\/strong> search by filters module (https:\/\/addons.prestashop.com\/en\/search-filters\/87818-advanced-search-5-search-by-filters.html) or <strong>its Pro version <\/strong>(https:\/\/addons.prestashop.com\/en\/search-filters\/2778-advanced-search-5-pro-filters-and-facets-seo.html), you further increase the search relevance in your catalog.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/div>\r\n\r\n<div>Our module is also compatible with the PrestaShop faceted search native module.<\/div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/div>\r\n\r\n<div><strong>Import your features and their multiple values in bulk action!<\/strong><\/div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>\r\n\r\n<div>Use the PrestaShop native CSV import tool to assign in bulk, and in a specific order, feature values to your products.<\/div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>\r\n\r\n<div>In your &quot;Products&quot; CSV import file, use the &quot;Feature(Name:Value:Position)&quot; column to define for each feature the values to be assigned to each product. Indicate in the module configuration the character used to separate the different values and that&#39;s it!<\/div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;<\/div>\r\n\r\n<div><strong>Example:<\/strong>&nbsp;Separator used: |<\/div>\r\n\r\n<div>Material:Yellow gold|White gold,Type of gemstone:Diamond This product will therefore be assigned 2 values of the feature &quot;Material&quot;, and a single value of the feature &quot;Type of gemstone&quot;.<\/div>\r\n","tab":"search_filter","version":"1.6.4","compatibility":{"from":"1.7.4.0","to":"8.1.2"},"nbRates":"220","product_type":"module","avgRate":"4.6","price":{"EUR":69.99,"USD":79.99,"GBP":62.99},"badges":[{"label":"Modules Partner Creator","img":"https:\/\/medias2.prestastore.com\/themes\/prestastore\/